      "text": "The Soho area has been at the heart of London's [[sex industry]] for over 200 years; between 1778 and 1801 21 Soho Square ([[Manor House, 21 Soho Square]]) was location of the White House, a [[brothel]] described by the magistrate [[Henry Mayhew]] as \"a notorious place of ill-fame\". - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soho#Sex_industry wikipedia]"
