      "text": "Before the [[Street Offences Act 1959]] became law, prostitutes packed Piccadilly Circus and the streets and alleys around Soho. By the early 1960s the area was home to nearly a hundred strip clubs and almost every doorway in Soho had red-lit doorbells, or open doors with little postcards just inside advertising \"Large Chest for Sale\" or \"French Lessons Given.\" These are known as walk-ups ([[Soho walk-up]]). "
